- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with resolving concurrent modifications in a distributed system.
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper discusses a data structure and algorithm for modifying and replicating data.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper presents a new datatype for JSON.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of the algorithm and its suitability for deployment on mobile devices and messaging systems.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the semantics of modifying a JSON data structure.
